{
  "info": {
    "name": "USI Payout Microservice (Internal)",
    "description": "Postman collection for the internal USI Payout microservice.\n\n## Authentication\n\nThis collection drives the **4-factor strong auth** described in the README:\n  1. `x-api-key`\n  2. a custom secret header (name + value)\n  3. `x-signature` + `x-timestamp` + `x-nonce` (HMAC-SHA256)\n  4. `Idempotency-Key` on payout endpoints\n\nA collection-level **pre-request script** generates all of these automatically before every request, including:\n  - SHA-256 of the (variable-resolved) body\n  - HMAC-SHA256 signature over the canonical string\n  - Fresh timestamp, nonce, correlation id\n  - Idempotency-Key for `POST /v1/transactions/` and `POST /v1/transactions/confirm`\n\n## Setup\n\nSet these collection variables to match ONE entry from your `INTERNAL_CLIENTS` secret:\n  - `baseUrl`             e.g. http://localhost:8080\n  - `apiKey`              x-api-key value for this client\n  - `secretHeaderName`    e.g. x-app-secret-token\n  - `secretHeaderValue`   value for that header\n  - `signingSecret`       HMAC-SHA256 signing key\n\nOptional:\n  - `idempotencyKey`      pin a specific Idempotency-Key (otherwise a fresh UUID is generated per request)\n\n⚠️ Do NOT commit a Postman environment file containing production secrets.\n\n## Endpoints\n\nAll business endpoints are mounted under `/v1`. createTransaction's test script captures `trans_session_id` into the collection variable so the next `confirmTransaction` call just works.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "9d1f2c0e-1a4a-4f8a-9bd0-000000000001"
  },
  "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8080", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "apiKey", "value": "ak_live_REPLACE_ME", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "secretHeaderName", "value": "x-app-secret-token", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "secretHeaderValue", "value": "sv_live_REPLACE_ME", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "signingSecret", "value": "sk_live_REPLACE_ME", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "idempotencyKey", "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "Optional. If empty, a fresh UUID is generated for every payout request." },
    { "key": "remitterId", "value": "10005", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "beneficiaryId", "value": "11", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "transRef", "value": "RA000263000102", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "agentTransRef", "value": "AGT-TEST-001", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "transSessionId", "value": "830016270356710161", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "auditId", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// =======================================================================",
          "// USI Payout Microservice — Strong-auth signer",
          "// Mirrors src/middleware/auth.ts on the server.",
          "// =======================================================================",
          "",
          "const url = pm.request.url;",
          "let pathOnly;",
          "try {",
          "  pathOnly = new URL(pm.variables.replaceIn(url.toString())).pathname;",
          "} catch (e) {",
          "  pathOnly = '/' + ((url.path || []).map((s) => pm.variables.replaceIn(s)).join('/'));",
          "}",
          "",
          "const apiKey            = pm.collectionVariables.get('apiKey');",
          "",
          "// ---- helpers (defined early so the audit branch can use them) -------",
          "function setHeader(name, value) {",
          "  const lower = name.toLowerCase();",
          "  const existing = pm.request.headers.find((h) => h && h.key && h.key.toLowerCase() === lower);",
          "  if (existing) existing.value = String(value);",
          "  else pm.request.headers.add({ key: name, value: String(value) });",
          "}",
          "",
          "// Skip auth on public endpoints (healthz, readyz). Their requests already set auth: noauth.",
          "if (pathOnly === '/healthz' || pathOnly === '/readyz') {",
          "  if (!pm.request.headers.has('x-correlation-id')) {",
          "    pm.request.headers.add({ key: 'x-correlation-id', value: 'pm-' + Date.now().toString(36) });",
          "  }",
          "  return;",
          "}",
          "",
          "// Audit endpoints accept x-api-key ONLY — no signature, no secret-header,",
          "// no nonce. Skip all of that and just set the api-key + correlation id.",
          "if (pathOnly.startsWith('/v1/audit')) {",
          "  if (apiKey) setHeader('x-api-key', apiKey);",
          "  if (!pm.request.headers.has('x-correlation-id')) {",
          "    setHeader('x-correlation-id', 'pm-' + Date.now().toString(36));",
          "  }",
          "  return;",
          "}",
          "",
          "const secretHeaderName  = (pm.collectionVariables.get('secretHeaderName') || '').toLowerCase();",
          "const secretHeaderValue = pm.collectionVariables.get('secretHeaderValue');",
          "const signingSecret     = pm.collectionVariables.get('signingSecret');",
          "",
          "if (!apiKey || !secretHeaderName || !secretHeaderValue || !signingSecret) {",
          "  console.warn('[strong-auth] One or more of apiKey / secretHeaderName / secretHeaderValue / signingSecret is unset. Set them in the collection Variables tab.');",
          "  return;",
          "}",
          "",
          "// ---- 1. resolve body (with {{vars}} substituted) -----------------------",
          "let bodyStr = '';",
          "if (pm.request.body && pm.request.body.mode === 'raw' && pm.request.body.raw) {",
          "  bodyStr = pm.variables.replaceIn(pm.request.body.raw);",
          "} else if (pm.request.body && pm.request.body.mode === 'urlencoded') {",
          "  // Build the form-encoded body the same way Postman would send it.",
          "  const parts = [];",
          "  pm.request.body.urlencoded.each((f) => {",
          "    if (f.disabled || !f.key) return;",
          "    parts.push(encodeURIComponent(pm.variables.replaceIn(f.key)) + '=' + encodeURIComponent(pm.variables.replaceIn(f.value || '')));",
          "  });",
          "  bodyStr = parts.join('&');",
          "}",
          "",
          "// ---- 2. sorted query (key=value pairs, lexicographically sorted) -------",
          "const queryItems = (url.query && url.query.all ? url.query.all() : [])",
          "  .filter((q) => q && !q.disabled && q.key)",
          "  .map((q) => pm.variables.replaceIn(q.key) + '=' + pm.variables.replaceIn(q.value || ''))",
          "  .sort();",
          "const sortedQuery = queryItems.join('&');",
          "",
          "// ---- 3. SHA-256 of body ------------------------------------------------",
          "const bodyHash = CryptoJS.SHA256(bodyStr).toString(CryptoJS.enc.Hex);",
          "",
          "// ---- 4. timestamp + nonce ---------------------------------------------",
          "const ts = String(Date.now());",
          "const nonce = 'pm-' + Date.now().toString(36) + '-' + Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 14);",
          "",
          "// ---- 5. canonical string + HMAC ---------------------------------------",
          "const method = pm.request.method.toUpperCase();",
          "const canonical = [method, pathOnly, sortedQuery, bodyHash, ts, nonce].join('\\n');",
          "const signature = CryptoJS.HmacSHA256(canonical, signingSecret).toString(CryptoJS.enc.Hex);",
          "",
          "// ---- 6. set auth headers ----------------------------------------------",
          "setHeader('x-api-key',       apiKey);",
          "setHeader(secretHeaderName,  secretHeaderValue);",
          "setHeader('x-timestamp',     ts);",
          "setHeader('x-nonce',         nonce);",
          "setHeader('x-signature',     signature);",
          "",
          "// ---- 7. correlation id -------------------------------------------------",
          "if (!pm.request.headers.has('x-correlation-id')) {",
          "  setHeader('x-correlation-id', 'pm-' + Date.now().toString(36));",
          "}",
          "",
          "// ---- 8. Idempotency-Key for payout endpoints ---------------------------",
          "// Server requires it for POST /v1/transactions/ and POST /v1/transactions/confirm.",
          "const PAYOUT_PATHS = ['/v1/transactions', '/v1/transactions/', '/v1/transactions/confirm'];",
          "const stripTrailing = pathOnly.replace(/\\/+$/, '');",
          "if (method === 'POST' && PAYOUT_PATHS.indexOf(pathOnly) !== -1) {",
          "  if (!pm.request.headers.has('idempotency-key')) {",
          "    const fixed = pm.collectionVariables.get('idempotencyKey');",
          "    let key = fixed && fixed.length >= 8 ? fixed : null;",
          "    if (!key) {",
          "      try {",
          "        key = (typeof crypto !== 'undefined' && crypto.randomUUID) ? crypto.randomUUID() : null;",
          "      } catch (e) { key = null; }",
          "      if (!key) key = 'idem-' + Date.now().toString(36) + '-' + Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 14);",
          "    }",
          "    setHeader('Idempotency-Key', key);",
          "  }",
          "}",
          "",
          "// ---- 9. debug (uncomment if you need to inspect the signing payload) ----",
          "// console.log('canonical:\\n' + canonical);",
          "// console.log('signature: ' + signature);"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Capture audit_id from any successful response so the next Audit request can use it.",
          "try {",
          "  const j = pm.response.json();",
          "  if (j && j.meta && j.meta.audit_id) pm.collectionVariables.set('auditId', j.meta.audit_id);",
          "  if (j && j.error && j.error.audit_id) pm.collectionVariables.set('auditId', j.error.audit_id);",
          "} catch (_) { /* non-JSON responses */ }"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
